cases.question:
A bibliography audit found an entry whose DOI is real but appears attached to the wrong paper. Determine whether the citation is internally consistent. Return only valid JSON in this schema:

{"consistent": false, "problem": "...", "corrected_title": "..."}

Entry to audit:

```bibtex
@inproceedings{badtriviaqa,
  title = {Attention is All You Need},
  author = {Vaswani, Ashish and Shazeer, Noam and Parmar, Niki},
  booktitle = {Proceedings of the 55th Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics},
  year = {2017},
  doi = {10.18653/v1/P17-1147}
}
```

The DOI and venue line are from the real SkillsBench citation-check bibliography. Audit the DOI/title consistency, not whether the title itself is a real paper.
